Package: GeoPaletteR
Type: Package
Title: Colour Space Conversions for Geospatial Raster Data
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: person("Igor", "Pawelec", email = "igor.pawelec@urk.edu.pl",
                  role = c("aut", "cre"),
                  comment = c(ORCID = "0009-0005-9798-3596"))
Description: Converts red-green-blue raster bands into fifteen colour
    spaces used in remote sensing, image segmentation and forestry, among
    them CIELAB, CIELUV, DIN99, Oklab, CIECAM02 and Jzazbz, with inverse
    transforms back to red-green-blue for four of them. Operations are
    vectorised over whole bands, so a scene is converted without looping
    over pixels, and the package is plain R with no compiled code and no
    required dependencies. Results track the 'GeoPalette' Python package,
    which stores intermediates in single precision where R has only
    double, so agreement is to that precision rather than exact; the
    tolerances are measured and documented. Colour appearance modelling
    follows Moroney and others (2002) for CIECAM02, Safdar and others
    (2017) <doi:10.1364/OE.25.015131> for Jzazbz, and Ottosson (2020) for
    Oklab.
